snippet.textDisplay: Metric vs Imperial? Basically, the only metric we deal with more than anything else is when it comes to nuts and bolts, other than that we use the Imperial system, inches and feet. Anything else that you do is inches, measuring wood, steel, clothing, tires, miles/ footage, the cost to change America to the metric system would cost billions if not trillions, metric has its place in certain applications, but for 98% of America the imperial system is what we know. Personally, I prefer SAE, but that's just me,  love the videos, keep them coming!
